The Karen Hospital, through the Heart to Heart Foundation, has donated face masks and gloves to Langata police division. The donations aim to facilitate a clean and safe environment and also to appreciate the selfless service by the officers in safeguarding the community and Kenyans at large during these tough times. They targeted over 400 police officers under the Langata division, including Langata, Karen, Nyayo, Hardy, Akila, Highrise, Bypass, Nairobi West and Westpark police stations.